    <section id="advisory" class="section reveal reveal-up">
      <h2>Advisory Council &amp; Meeting Cadence</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Many workgroups meet on a consistent rhythm, often aligned with the Advisory Council, while a few
        committees meet only as needed or for special processes like hearings.
      </p>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <article class="highlight-band">
          <div class="highlight-strip"></div>
          <div class="highlight-title">What to Expect When You Serve</div>
          <p class="highlight-body">
            Time commitments vary by committee, but most workgroups are designed to be manageable alongside a
            full-time real estate career. Many meetings are held via Zoom or grouped on Advisory Council days.
          </p>
          <ul class="highlight-list">
            <li><strong>Monthly on Zoom:</strong> Media Committee, MLS Committee</li>
            <li><strong>Monthly during Advisory Council:</strong> Events, Global Diversity, YPN, Professional Development, Magazine, RPAC/Government Affairs</li>
            <li><strong>As needed:</strong> Professional Standards &amp; Grievance (with required training)</li>
            <li><strong>2‚Äì3 times per year:</strong> Leadership Development Committee</li>
            <li><strong>Full-year program:</strong> Leadership Academy (application &amp; interview required)</li>
            <li><strong>Next step:</strong> Complete the
              <a href="https://bonitaspringsesterorealtorsfl.growthzoneapp.com/ap/Form/Fill/LbnDeCKL" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2026 Consent to Serve form</a>.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h3>Advisory Council Connection</h3>
          <p>
            The Advisory Council serves as a hub where committee reports, updates, and ideas come together.
            Several of the ‚ÄúWorkgroup‚Äù committees meet directly before or during Advisory Council blocks, making
            it easier to serve without overloading your calendar.
          </p>
          <p class="meta-line">
            When you complete the 2026 Consent to Serve, simply mark the committees you‚Äôre interested in ‚Äî staff will follow up with specifics.
